  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "On the swamp-choked world of Bacchus, the Imperium is losing its air war against an Ork incursion and would rather sell a triumph than admit the front is collapsing. Propagandist Kile Simlex arrives to turn Flight Commander Lucille von Shard, a brilliant and poisonous Aeronautica Imperialis ace, into a cinema hero for the war effort. Instead he finds retreating squadrons, a governor massaging the truth, and Shard burning through pilots as fast as the greenskin tide burns territory. Then something vast begins to move in the clouds. A cockpit war-story about propaganda, cowardice, and the lie of Imperial heroism.",
